<h2><a name="fread" id="fread">fread</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstdio&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">int</span> fread<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">void</span> <span class="sy0">*</span>buffer<span class="sy0">,</span> size_t size<span class="sy0">,</span> size_t num<span class="sy0">,</span> FILE <span class="sy0">*</span>stream <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;</pre>
<p>
The function fread() reads num number of objects (where each object is size
bytes) and places them into the array pointed to by buffer.
</p>

<p>
The data comes from the given input stream.
</p>

<p>
The return value of the function is the number of things read. You can use <a href="feof" class="wikilink1" title="c:io:feof">feof</a> or <a href="ferror" class="wikilink1" title="c:io:ferror">ferror</a> to figure out if an error occurs.
</p>

<p>
